# Many of the duchies, counties & baronies are named after geographical features and overall regions
# The vast majority of cities are fairly modern, at the very least from Renaissance era

# Northern & western sides of the Baïkal are set as shamanic instead of tengri
# In reality, it's difficult to say because of the lack of records, and because there very likely was a lot of shamano-tengric syncretism
# Olkhon and very northern lands are set as shamanic, while the Uda Valley and close-by Dauria are set as Tengri

#Mongol mostly removed as a culture in this region and clan breakdowns used. Mongol is still used for dynasties of unknown clan affiliation and in post Mongol conquest areas to represent multiple clans being present in the area until the later bookmarks where the new cultures (chagatai, tatar etc.) come to exist


# Many of the duchies, counties & baronies are named after geographical features and overall regions
# The vast majority of cities are fairly modern, at the very least from Renaissance era

#k_mongolia

###c_karakorum
1457 = {	#Karakorum
	#Historical capital of the Mongol Empire, founded in the XIIIth
	culture = uyghur
    religion = manichean
	holding = tribal_holding
	867.1.1 = {
		buildings = {
			longhouses_01
		}
	}

        culture = tongra
    }

        culture = kerait
		religion = eastern_tengri
    }
	
	1204.1.1 = {
        culture = mongol
    }
	
	1337.1.1 = {
		holding = castle_holding
		religion = lamaism			
		buildings = {
			curtain_walls_01
			farm_estates_01
			barracks_01
			pastures_01
		}
	}
}

}

#Most of the settlements with no specific notes are somewhat placeholder-ish
#Because of the lack of population density and relevant settlements in the area, there are many placeholders named after small settlements or geographical features
